tspan.tspan: VMC is a model for the growth of artificial structures over time, it draws ispiration
from plant's morphogenesis. It captures the dynamics of resource distribution in
tree-shaped structures, where branches compete to grow.
In VMC, nodes in a tree structure collect and transmit success from the environment
or child nodes to their parent. This success influences the thickness of vascular
pathways, regulating the distribution of resources from root to leaves.
